**Hamilton Comedian Eric Johnston Joins Canadian Comedy Hall of Fame Comedy Festival as Committee Member**

**Hamilton, Ontario** — In an exciting development for the Canadian comedy scene, Eric Johnston, a well-known comedian hailing from Hamilton, Ontario, has been appointed as an official committee member for the upcoming Canadian Comedy Hall of Fame Comedy Festival set to take place in early 2024. 

Eric Johnston's extensive experience and undeniable talent make him a natural fit for this important role. As a committee member, Johnston will play a vital role in shaping the festival's lineup, programming, and overall direction. His responsibilities will encompass helping book top-tier comedic talent, developing engaging programming, seeking out sponsors, and even gracing the festival stage himself to deliver his signature brand of humor.

Johnston's involvement in the festival is expected to infuse fresh energy and innovation into the event. With his deep connections within the comedy industry and his intimate knowledge of the Hamilton community, he is poised to contribute significantly to the festival's success.

"I am so thrilled to be a part of the Canadian Comedy Hall of Fame Comedy Festival coming to Hamilton," Johnston commented. "Being able to help bring together hilarious talent, create amazing shows, and showcase the vibrant comedic culture in Hamilton is a dream come true for me. I can't wait to collaborate with fellow committee members to make this festival an amazing success. Everybody used to laugh AT Hamilton now it’s time to laugh WITH us!"

The Canadian Comedy Hall of Fame Comedy Festival promises to be a highlight of the comedy calendar, offering attendees a diverse and dynamic lineup of performances, workshops, and events including an induction of the @canadiancomedyhallof class of 2023! As a committee member, Eric Johnston's contributions will undoubtedly elevate the festival's impact and entertainment value.

Join the Canadian Comedy Hall Of Fame TODAY and vote in your class of 2023! 

https://canadiancomedyhall.com

Years ago I was up for a role in a TV playing a cowboy and production was absolutely adamant that I knew how to ride a horse.  Being the hustler I am I told my agent that I had “grown up riding horses on my uncles farm”, I had not, I hadn’t even seen a horse up close in my life before… I got cast and thought “I’ll figure it out before we film” but ultimately the production got scrapped pre-production. 

Cut to last night I surprised Janna with a private sunset horseback riding tour through the jungle and across the Nosara beach for our honeymoon / her birthday tomorrow and in booking the tour the guide asked me if I knew how to ride a horse in which I responded “of course, I grew up riding horses on my uncles farm!”… I still had not. Janna actually grew up going to horse camp every summer so she’s a pro… me, I’m just full of shit. 

Long story short I was a natural! I was absolutely calm and in control the entire time through the jungle and across the beach, I had steering, I had speed, I had braking. it was one of the most beautiful experiences of my life. I fessed up to the guide that I was my first time and he was SHOCKED! He said I was a natural! (Almost like I grew up going to horse camp!) 

Sometimes I pays off to be a little full of shit, because ultimately… life is like riding a HORSE! 

Also: immediately adding “EXTENSIVE HORSE TRAINING AND RIDING EXPERIENCE” to my acting resume… 

🐎🌊☀️🌴

Carmen’s Live Presents: An Evening with Eric Johnston & Friends! 

Hamilton, Ontario - Carmen’s Event Centre is thrilled to announce a night of hilarious stand up comedy with “An Evening with Eric Johnston & Friends” on Friday, November 10th, 2023. 

Eric Johnston, a seasoned professional stand-up comedian hailing from Hamilton, Ontario, with an impressive 13-year comedy career, is set to take the stage for a side-splitting 75-minute performance that promises non-stop hilarity and story telling.

The evening kicks off with a lineup of Eric’s closest friends and top-tier stand-up comedians, guaranteeing a night filled with unforgettable performances. These comics have been hand picked by Eric and he promises they are the best up and coming comics in Canada . 

Eric Johnston’s comedic talent has graced screens big and small, in 170 countries across the world, with appearances on YTV, MTV, Crave TV, Vice TV, Apple TV, Amazon Prime US/UK, among others. His unique brand of high energy humour has left audiences in stitches nationwide with several sold out coast to coast tours! 

Not only a television sensation, Eric has also left his mark on some of the most iconic comedy venues in the United States. His live performances at the Laugh Factory in Chicago, The Comedy Store in Los Angeles, and the House of Blues in Chicago have solidified his reputation as a comedic force to be reckoned with.

Don’t miss this chance to catch Eric Johnston’s live comedy brilliance in the heart of Hamilton. Tickets are available now for $50 + fees and are expected to sell out quickly. Secure your spot for a night of laughter, great food & drinks and even a professional cigar roller!

- Hamilton based stand-up comedian Eric Johnston is set to bring laughter, joy, and holiday spirit to corporate Christmas parties and office gatherings of all sizes. With his comedic talent and engaging stage presence, Eric offers a side-splitting and unforgettable experience that will have employees and colleagues rolling in the aisles.

As the holiday season approaches, companies are seeking innovative ways to celebrate and connect with their teams. Eric Johnston's corporate comedy performances provide a unique and entertaining solution for a memorable holiday event. His relatable humor and sharp wit ensure that attendees of all backgrounds and personalities will find themselves entertained.

Eric's performances are tailor-made to suit the tone and preferences of each event, making him the perfect choice for office parties, Christmas galas, and year-end celebrations. With a keen understanding of corporate dynamics, Eric effortlessly weaves hilarious stories about his life  and his high energy style, creating a shared unforgettable experience. 

"Laughter is what bringe people together, especially during the holiday season," says Eric Johnston. "My goal is create such a great environment that people forget their busy work year and life and just sit back and enjoy the show with their coworkers."

Whether it's a small team gathering or a grand corporate gala, Eric's performances are guaranteed to leave a lasting impression. His ability to find humor in everyday office scenarios and holiday traditions ensures that his comedy resonates with audiences across the board.

Companies looking to infuse their holiday events with laughter and a lighthearted touch can book Eric Johnston for an unforgettable comedic experience. His performances promise to be a highlight of the holiday season, leaving employees talking and laughing long after the event has ended.

Hamilton based Comedian and Actor Eric Johnston to Inspire Students at Mohawk College's Radio & Creative Content Program

HAMILTON, ON – Eric Johnston, the renowned Canadian comedian and actor, is set to make a special appearance as a guest speaker at Mohawk College's Radio & Creative Content program. Johnston will deliver an engaging talk on the art of self-marketing and branding, offering valuable insights to aspiring broadcasters and entertainers.

Date: Wed, Oct 4th, 2023
Time: 9:30 AM

Eric Johnston's extensive experience in the world of entertainment and comedy has earned him recognition and respect throughout Canada. With a knack for both humor and marketing, Johnston will share his expertise on building a personal brand and effectively marketing oneself in the competitive entertainment industry.

This talk promises to be an enlightening and interactive experience for students, providing them with practical knowledge and tips to navigate the evolving media landscape. Eric Johnston's unique blend of comedy and marketing savvy is sure to leave a lasting impression.

Run with the Bull: 

I don’t know where to begin on this because I’m not sure that it was something that I ever thought I’d be writing… 

For the last year I’ve been secretly writing a book. 

I’ve partnered with Greg Oliver who is a legendary and celebrated sports writer who has written 20 books and has been a wrestling and sports writer for decades as well as the producer of SlamWrestling.net. I met him when he wrote my father’s obituary and attended his funeral in 2003.

Over a year ago Greg approached me and said “I look at your life and there is a book here”. 

The book details the life stories and careers of my grandfather Ron “Bull” Johnston, my father Danny “Bullwhip” Johnston and my journey into show business following in the footsteps of the giants who walked before me. 

There’s stories and interviews from wrestling legends and even some of my dads buddies from the east end of Hamilton. 

The book is both heartbreaking and hilarious. It is a story of massive victories and shattering defeats. The book talks about love and loss, addiction and pain and travels many highways across North American and as far as Japan.  Mostly important it tells a tale of many roads leading back to Hamilton, Ontario. 

One of my longest friends and one of the most talented people I know @mattryan has designed the front and back covers and they are simply the most beautiful pieces of art I’ve ever seen. I look at it and see my city and see my story and that’s all I’ve ever wanted to get out there. 

This book is the most important thing I’ve done in show business and I am so privileged and honoured to share it with everyone who’s Run with the Bull 

“Run with the Bull: 3 Generations of Sports & Entertainment” will be available to pre order before Christmas and available in the new year. Followed by a massive book launch and celebration in Hamilton. 

🐂❤️💪🏽

70 Years Old: 

The thing about time is it just keeps going but for some reason this milestone is really hitting hard for me today. Today January 7th 2024 my dad would have been 70 years old. It’s the first time I think about him and picture an old man. I didn’t know my father as a young man, I only have stories. I only got 13 years of him ages 37 - 49 I only have memories and from ages 49 to now I only have my imagination. My imagination is always so strong with him but for some reason I’m having a hard time picturing him as an old man. I think he would be doing everything he could to look young. I think he’d be dying his hair and tanning. Shit I think he’d still lace up the boots and pull out the whip to let us know he’s still got it. But I also a picture a man who aged gracefully, a clean shaven man with grey hair and only the finest track suits (that fell off the back of a truck). No matter what version I picture him the look on his face is pride. As you can see I’m doing everything I can to keep his name alive, I’m taking him with me everywhere I go. I said years ago “when you lose a parent at a young age you spend the rest of your life seeking approval from someone you’re never going to get it from” but I really feel over the last year of getting married to the love of my life @janna.leigh and moving into our dream home, working hard to make my career explode I really feel the approval washing over me. I feel at peace with the whole story. Now it’s time for me to be my own man, with my own story, be my own bull and hopefully soon create a little bull of my own. This promise I give to him on his 70th birthday. 🐂❤️
